    "### Rolling Feature Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "Rolling features summarize recent behavior over a defined window, capturing both the average state and variability of process variables over time.\n",
    "\n",
    "We computed:\n",
    "- **Rolling mean (10-step window)** → short-term trend\n",
    "- **Rolling standard deviation (10-step window)** → short-term variability\n",
    "\n",
    "Since the data is sampled every minute, this represents approximately the **last 10 minutes of operation**.\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Key Observations\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Short-term trend smoothing**  \n",
    "  The rolling mean reduces noise and highlights the underlying direction of each variable, making it easier to identify gradual drifts and sustained changes in the process.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Instability detection through variability**  \n",
    "  The rolling standard deviation captures fluctuations within the window:\n",
    "  - low values → stable operation  \n",
    "  - high values → increased instability or oscillations  \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Early fault indication**  \n",
    "  Faults often develop with increasing variability before extreme values occur.  \n",
    "  Rolling statistics help detect:\n",
    "  - vibration buildup  \n",
    "  - pressure oscillations  \n",
    "  - unstable reaction conditions  \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Reactor-specific behavior preserved**  \n",
    "  Calculations are performed within each `reactor_id`, ensuring that rolling patterns reflect each reactor’s own dynamics rather than mixing across units.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Robust to noise**  \n",
    "  By aggregating multiple time steps, rolling features reduce sensitivity to random noise while retaining meaningful signals.\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Expected NaN values**  \n",
    "  At the beginning of each reactor’s time series, fewer than 10 observations are available, leading to partial or missing values.  \n",
    "  This is expected and handled using `min_periods=1`.\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "Rolling features provide a powerful representation of recent system behavior, capturing both trends and instability. They are particularly valuable for detecting evolving faults and improving the model’s ability to identify abnormal process conditions."
   ]
