    "### Fault History Feature Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "Fault history features track the **recent occurrence of faults over a rolling window**, allowing the model to understand temporal patterns in failure behavior.\n",
    "\n",
    "We construct:\n",
    "- **is_fault** → binary indicator (1 = fault, 0 = normal)\n",
    "- **fault_rolling_count_20** → number of faults in the last 20 time steps\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Key Observations\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Captures fault persistence**\n",
    "  Faults often do not occur in isolation. A recent fault increases the likelihood of:\n",
    "  - continued instability  \n",
    "  - repeated failures  \n",
    "  - system degradation  \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Detects fault clustering**\n",
    "  Higher rolling counts indicate:\n",
    "  - bursts of faults  \n",
    "  - periods of unstable operation  \n",
    "  - possible cascading failures  \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Early warning signal**\n",
    "  Even before a major fault occurs, an increase in recent fault activity can signal:\n",
    "  - deteriorating system health  \n",
    "  - approaching failure conditions  \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Temporal dependency awareness**\n",
    "  The model can now learn:\n",
    "  - “what just happened”  \n",
    "  - not just “what is happening now”  \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Improves predictive power**\n",
    "  Historical fault context helps distinguish:\n",
    "  - isolated anomalies (low risk)  \n",
    "  - sustained issues (high risk)  \n",
    "\n",
    "#### Example Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "- Value = 0 → no recent faults (stable system)  \n",
    "- Low values (1–3) → occasional faults  \n",
    "- High values → fault-prone period / unstable regime  \n",
    "\n",
    "#### Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "Fault history features introduce **memory into the model**, enabling it to detect patterns of instability over time and significantly improving fault prediction in time-series systems."
   ]
