   "source": [
    "### Spike / Threshold-Based Feature Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "Spike features identify **unusually high values** in key variables by applying statistical thresholds. These features convert continuous signals into **binary indicators of abnormal behavior**.\n",
    "\n",
    "We construct:\n",
    "- **vibration_spike_flag** → 1 if vibration exceeds threshold  \n",
    "- **power_spike_flag** → 1 if power consumption exceeds threshold  \n",
    "\n",
    "Where threshold =  \n",
    "`mean + 2 × standard deviation`\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Key Observations\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Captures extreme events**\n",
    "  These features highlight rare but important events such as:\n",
    "  - sudden vibration surges  \n",
    "  - abnormal power spikes  \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Strong fault indicators**\n",
    "  From EDA, faults are often associated with:\n",
    "  - sharp spikes rather than gradual changes  \n",
    "  - short-lived but intense deviations  \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Noise filtering**\n",
    "  By using a statistical threshold, we ignore:\n",
    "  - normal fluctuations  \n",
    "  - minor variations  \n",
    "  and focus only on **significant anomalies**\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Simplifies model learning**\n",
    "  Binary flags make it easier for models to:\n",
    "  - detect abnormal states  \n",
    "  - learn decision boundaries  \n",
    "  especially for tree-based models  \n",
    "\n",
    "- **Early warning signals**\n",
    "  Spikes can occur:\n",
    "  - before a fault is officially recorded  \n",
    "  - during the onset of instability  \n",
    "\n",
    "#### Example Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "- Value = 0 → normal operating range  \n",
    "- Value = 1 → abnormal spike detected  \n",
    "\n",
    "- Frequent spikes → unstable system behavior  \n",
    "- Isolated spikes → possible transient disturbances  \n",
    "\n",
    "#### Engineering Insight\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Vibration spikes** → mechanical issues (imbalance, wear, misalignment)  \n",
    "- **Power spikes** → inefficiency, overload, or process disruption  \n",
    "\n",
    "#### Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "Spike features act as **high-sensitivity anomaly detectors**, capturing sudden deviations that are strongly linked to faults and improving the model’s ability to detect critical events in real time."
   ]
