    "### Missing Values After Feature Engineering — Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "Missing values introduced by lag and rolling operations are expected and structured, not random.\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Key Observations\n",
    "\n",
    "- These missing values occur at the beginning of each reactor sequence\n",
    "- They result from insufficient historical context\n",
    "- They should not be treated as general data quality issues\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Why this approach is better\n",
    "\n",
    "Instead of dropping every row with any missing value, we:\n",
    "- remove only the minimum number of lag-affected rows\n",
    "- preserve as much normal and fault data as possible\n",
    "- keep the dataset suitable for supervised learning\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Conclusion\n",
    "\n",
    "This missing-value strategy preserves class balance and temporal structure much better than a blanket `dropna()`."
   ]
