    "---\n",
    "## Feature Engineering Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "In this notebook, we transformed raw time-series sensor data into a rich set of features designed to capture temporal dynamics, system behavior, and early fault signals.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### What We Engineered\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 1. Time-Based Features\n",
    "- Hour, day, day of week, and month extracted from timestamps  \n",
    "- Capture **operational cycles and scheduling effects**\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 2. Lag Features\n",
    "- 1, 5, and 10-step lags for key variables  \n",
    "- Represent **recent system history (1–10 minutes ago)**  \n",
    "\n",
    "> Helps models understand **temporal dependencies and gradual fault buildup**\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 3. Rate-of-Change Features\n",
    "- First-order differences between current and previous values  \n",
    "\n",
    "Captures:\n",
    "- sudden jumps  \n",
    "- short-term instability  \n",
    "- abnormal transitions  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 4. Rolling Statistics\n",
    "- Rolling mean and standard deviation (window = 10)  \n",
    "\n",
    "Captures:\n",
    "- local trends (mean)  \n",
    "- variability and volatility (std)  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 5. Regime-Based Features\n",
    "- Deviation from mean behavior within each operating regime  \n",
    "\n",
    "Highlights:\n",
    "- **contextual anomalies**  \n",
    "- deviations relative to \"normal\" conditions  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 6. Interaction Features\n",
    "- Combined effects between key variables (e.g., temp × pressure)\n",
    "\n",
    "Captures:\n",
    "- **nonlinear relationships**  \n",
    "- system coupling effects  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
